Hello John,

Seeds are usually crawled in a relatively timely manner. If after a long time some seeds are showing up as NOTCRAWLED in the seed report, it could be that the sites have not been responding and that the seeds are on the slow retry cycle. Some additional analysis of config/reports/logs could reveal what&#39;s going on. How many seeds do you have, how many have not been crawled, what is being crawled instead, how busy is the crawl, any unusual config, and so forth. The particular thing you&#39;re asking about, crawling remaining seeds immediately ahead of anything else, may be possible but probably not trivial, and the way to do it (and whether it makes sense to try) depends on knowing more about the state of the crawl.

Noah

